SENATE . . . . . . . . . . . . . . No. 1003
By Mr. Kennedy, a petition (accompanied by resolve, Senate, No. 1003) of Edward J. Kennedy
that provisions be made for an investigation and study by a special commission (including
members of the General Court) to exam the comprehensive permit law for low or moderate
income housing under Chapter 40B. Housing.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
Resolve to examine Chapter 40B.
1 Resolved, there shall be a special commission to examine modernizing the
2 comprehensive permit law for low or moderate income housing under Chapter 40B.
3 The commission shall consist of the House and Senate chairs of the Joint Committee on
4 Housing, who shall serve as co-chairs of the special commission; the commissioner of the
5 Executive Office of Housing and Livable Communities or a designee; 1 member appointed by
6 the senate president; 1 member appointed by the senate minority leader; 1 member appointed by
7 the speaker of the house 1 member appointed by the house minority leader; 4 representatives of
8 cities and towns appointed by the Massachusetts Municipal Association; 1 representative of
9 community organizations involved in affordable housing development.
10 This commission shall thoroughly examine the comprehensive permit law and suggest
11 any amendments that would improve the law's effectiveness in balancing community needs with
12 the need for more housing in Massachusetts.
1 of 2

13 The first meeting of the commission shall take place not later than 2 months after this bill
14 is enactment into law. The commission shall submit its recommendations, together with drafts of
15 any legislation, to the clerks of the Senate and the House of Representatives, the chairs of the
16 Joint Committee on Housing, not later than December 31, 2025.
